<h2>
    Best Streams and Creeks for Wild Trout
</h2>
<h3>
    Upper Rogue River
</h3>
<p>
    This river is a trout mecca. Above Lost Creek Lake, the Rogue is managed as a wild trout fishery, offering strong populations of rainbows and cutthroats.
</p>
<h3>
    Little Butte Creek
</h3>
<p>
    A hidden gem that runs through Eagle Point and White City, Little Butte Creek offers peaceful settings and pockets of wild trout.
</p>
<h3>
    Applegate River
</h3>
<p>
    A great location for late spring and early summer trout fishing. It’s especially good for fly anglers targeting riffles and deep undercut banks.
</p>
<h2>
    Top Lakes and Reservoirs for Stocked Trout
</h2>
<h3>
    Hyatt Lake
</h3>
<p>
    Situated in the Cascade foothills, this lake is regularly stocked and offers beautiful views. Great for boat and shore fishing alike.
</p>
<h3>
    Howard Prairie Lake
</h3>
<p>
    Known for big rainbow trout and easy access. Fish from the shore or rent a boat for deeper waters.
</p>
<h3>
    Fish Lake
</h3>
<p>
    Ideal for summer trips, with rainbow and brook trout. There’s a resort nearby with cabin rentals and a boat launch.
</p>
<h3>
    Emigrant Lake
</h3>
<p>
    Just east of Medford, it offers solid spring and fall fishing for stocked rainbows. Close to town but scenic enough for a nature escape.
</p>
